indicator.description:
Output 1 indicators: National Border Management strategies reflect border communities pillar of African Union continental border management strategy, Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) and Economic Community of Central African States (ECCAS) peace and security strategies;
Output2 indicators: Min. 100 CoP members, #  repeat  visits to Knowledge Management (KM) site, CoP feedback questionnaires;
Output 3 indicators: Number of inclusive meetings held, quality and number of recommendations made, response of authorities and community feedback in regard to border management regime.

baseline.comment:
Output 1: Sahel countries do not have border management strategies in place, in spite of deterioration in security situation in border regions.
Output 2: Current lack of consistent reporting & dialogue, outdated statistics, action plans;
Output 3: Intermittent presence of Border Agencies in Border regions, and low level of interaction with local communities on security, facilitation & rights issues.
